1
00:00:00,461 --> 00:00:08,561
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

2
00:00:08,736 --> 00:00:16,973
<i>Even if you get lost, let's start walking</i>

3
00:00:17,211 --> 00:00:19,202
<i>One more time</i>

4
00:00:22,216 --> 00:00:25,982
<i>Are you really happy</i>

5
00:00:26,053 --> 00:00:29,420
<i>when you're always meeting</i>
<i>to someone's expectations?</i>

6
00:00:29,623 --> 00:00:33,184
<i>Even if you change to</i>
<i>who you really wanna be</i>

7
00:00:33,561 --> 00:00:36,928
<i>Will you always have a great smile?</i>

8
00:00:36,998 --> 00:00:44,427
<i>Dreaming of only "the beginning,"</i>
<i>I wake up</i>

9
00:00:44,505 --> 00:00:53,641
<i>and someday, I'll live on my own.</i>

10
00:00:53,714 --> 00:01:01,746
<i>Yes, precious things are never in shape</i>

11
00:01:01,989 --> 00:01:08,827
<i>You never know what it is</i>
<i>when you get it or lose it</i>

12
00:01:08,896 --> 00:01:16,962
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

13
00:01:17,271 --> 00:01:25,736
<i>Even if you get lost,</i>
<i>let's start walking</i>

14
00:01:25,813 --> 00:01:27,838
<i>One more time</i>

15
00:01:31,796 --> 00:01:34,594
Release the Genjutsu and
wake up Naruto and Shikamaru.

16
00:01:35,367 --> 00:01:36,800
He'll be getting a mission
after such a long while.

17
00:01:37,969 --> 00:01:39,197
What do you mean by a mission?

18
00:01:39,971 --> 00:01:41,165
Be careful...

19
00:01:42,941 --> 00:01:46,308
It's the first A Ranked mission
since the Land of the Waves.

20
00:01:51,483 --> 00:01:52,814
Ouch!

21
00:01:53,685 --> 00:01:55,880
You were able to release
the Genjutsu too!

22
00:01:56,254 --> 00:01:58,222
Why were you pretending
to be asleep?!

23
00:01:59,157 --> 00:02:01,921
Track down Sasuke,
join up and then stop him!

24
00:02:02,394 --> 00:02:05,192
Then await next orders
in a safe place.

25
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,062
Huh? Did something happen to Sasuke?!

26
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:10,066
I'll tell you the reason en route!

27
00:02:11,136 --> 00:02:11,966
Let's go

28
00:02:13,104 --> 00:02:14,071
H-Hey!

29
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:38,895
I get it! So that's what happened!

30
00:02:39,297 --> 00:02:41,857
That Sasuke, getting all impatient!

31
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:47,137
So, why am I pulled into this?
This is such a drag!

32
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,600
It can't be helped!

33
00:02:50,141 --> 00:02:52,075
It's Kakashi Sensei's order.

34
00:02:56,281 --> 00:02:56,940
This way!

35
00:03:00,452 --> 00:03:02,010
How long will it be until
we catch up?

36
00:03:02,287 --> 00:03:05,620
I don't know.
He is moving at a pretty good speed.

37
00:03:06,291 --> 00:03:07,519
Dang it!

38
00:03:11,162 --> 00:03:17,123
<i>A Shirker's Call to Action.</i>
<i>Layabout No More!</i>

39
00:03:39,924 --> 00:03:42,256
Hey! Hurry it up, you guys.

40
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,618
Huh? What is it?

41
00:03:43,795 --> 00:03:45,660
Did you find Sasuke?

42
00:03:46,130 --> 00:03:46,824
No!

43
00:03:47,165 --> 00:03:49,599
There are eight people in
two squads behind us...

44
00:03:50,068 --> 00:03:50,557
No...

45
00:03:51,469 --> 00:03:54,370
There's one more...
There are nine people following us.

46
00:03:54,572 --> 00:03:55,061
What?!

47
00:03:55,807 --> 00:03:59,208
C'mon. Already?!
Give me a break!

48
00:04:19,564 --> 00:04:23,398
It looks they haven't grasped
our location, yet.

49
00:04:27,772 --> 00:04:29,000
We must lose them.

50
00:04:39,551 --> 00:04:42,111
Hey, what's the point of stopping

51
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:44,378
Shut up and follow me!

52
00:04:44,756 --> 00:04:45,415
Huh?

53
00:04:47,892 --> 00:04:49,757
We're going back over our footprints.

54
00:04:50,461 --> 00:04:51,894
If we do that,

55
00:04:51,963 --> 00:04:53,931
it'll look to them like our footprints
suddenly disappeared.

56
00:04:57,569 --> 00:05:02,973
But, they'll notice even
if we do this, right?

57
00:05:03,474 --> 00:05:07,069
It'll buy us some time.
That's enough.

58
00:05:07,979 --> 00:05:12,643
It'll be a matter for great celebration
if our pursuers get impatient,

59
00:05:13,084 --> 00:05:16,451
cloud their eyes of pursuit
and lose sight of the trail.

60
00:05:18,590 --> 00:05:19,716
Hurry!

61
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:22,683
There's no time.

62
00:05:22,827 --> 00:05:24,920
I-I know!

63
00:05:50,588 --> 00:05:51,350
This is not good.

64
00:05:52,323 --> 00:05:54,484
Though they're on
alert for ambushes,

65
00:05:54,559 --> 00:05:56,220
they're catching up with us
slowly, but surely.

66
00:05:56,661 --> 00:05:57,787
Dang it!

67
00:05:58,429 --> 00:06:00,590
Probably they're all Chunin or higher.

68
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:03,258
We'll be wiped out if they catch up.

69
00:06:04,102 --> 00:06:05,000
<i>Wiped out...</i>

70
00:06:05,603 --> 00:06:09,664
Dang it! Since it's come to this,
why don't we ambush them?!

71
00:06:10,108 --> 00:06:11,040
Ambush?

72
00:06:11,843 --> 00:06:12,639
Right.

73
00:06:13,611 --> 00:06:16,136
Indeed, an ambush would
be to our advantage.

74
00:06:16,714 --> 00:06:19,410
Even if the opponent has twice
the people than we do,

75
00:06:20,018 --> 00:06:21,485
if we just catch them off guard...

76
00:06:22,053 --> 00:06:23,111
That's no good.

77
00:06:23,988 --> 00:06:27,446
Our opponents are former
Leaf Shinobi Orochimaru's henchmen.

78
00:06:28,259 --> 00:06:30,989
In the worst case scenario,
there might be Jonin.

79
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:35,831
I thought it'd work,
but I guess not, huh.

80
00:06:36,234 --> 00:06:38,168
Hold it. Why?

81
00:06:38,569 --> 00:06:41,800
The level of opponent doesn't have
much to do with an ambush.

82
00:06:42,473 --> 00:06:44,134
What do you mean?

83
00:06:44,876 --> 00:06:47,310
You guys don't get it.

84
00:06:47,945 --> 00:06:52,609
Listen. Indeed, an ambush is
a very advantageous fundamental tactic.

85
00:06:53,084 --> 00:06:56,053
But two conditions are necessary.

86
00:06:56,454 --> 00:06:59,116
What are those necessary conditions?

87
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:00,357
Number one.

88
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:05,255
The ones on the run must act without
making noise and find the enemy first.

89
00:07:06,397 --> 00:07:07,056
Number two.

90
00:07:07,865 --> 00:07:09,992
One must be able to catch
the pursuers off guard,

91
00:07:10,068 --> 00:07:14,061
capture a point and position
to be able to inflict certain damage

92
00:07:14,338 --> 00:07:16,135
and conceal oneself quickly.

93
00:07:16,974 --> 00:07:18,134
Ah... Huh?

94
00:07:18,676 --> 00:07:23,136
An ambush only becomes effective
when these two conditions are ensured.

95
00:07:25,283 --> 00:07:28,218
Well, the first condition
won't be so difficult

96
00:07:28,286 --> 00:07:29,981
since we have the Ninja Hound's nose.

97
00:07:30,621 --> 00:07:33,988
And the second one also
seems advantageous at a glance

98
00:07:34,058 --> 00:07:37,619
since we know the geography
of our village.

99
00:07:38,529 --> 00:07:41,157
But Orochimaru has spent time
in the Leaf before.

100
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:44,265
That approach won't work
on his henchmen.

101
00:07:45,603 --> 00:07:47,434
So what do you really mean?

102
00:07:47,772 --> 00:07:50,468
Our pursuers must have been instructed
in the terrain of this village

103
00:07:50,541 --> 00:07:54,477
and have gone through
simulated practice for this fight.

104
00:07:54,946 --> 00:07:55,776
And on top of that,

105
00:07:55,847 --> 00:07:59,749
they're probably all Ninja
who have mastered the pursuit arts.

106
00:08:00,485 --> 00:08:02,612
So they know what cards we have, huh.

107
00:08:03,154 --> 00:08:07,215
Well, even so, the fact remains
that an ambush is advantageous.

108
00:08:07,658 --> 00:08:09,387
But there are too many elements
of uncertainty.

109
00:08:09,994 --> 00:08:14,863
In the first place, the enemy is
a special unit organized for this operation.

110
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:18,197
But we have a fool...

111
00:08:18,803 --> 00:08:20,794
a Kunoichi who's nothing special...

112
00:08:22,039 --> 00:08:22,971
and one dog...

113
00:08:23,908 --> 00:08:27,071
and, me with the number one cold feet!

114
00:08:28,112 --> 00:08:31,912
A tactic is grasping the conditions
that are there without fail

115
00:08:32,049 --> 00:08:33,812
and formulating an optimal plan.

116
00:08:34,819 --> 00:08:38,778
And so, there's only one thing
that we can do now...

117
00:08:39,757 --> 00:08:40,416
One?

118
00:08:41,192 --> 00:08:43,854
A diversion in the guise
of an ambush.

119
00:08:44,662 --> 00:08:47,597
One person will remain,
pretend to ambush,

120
00:08:47,999 --> 00:08:49,296
and delay the pursuers.

121
00:08:51,235 --> 00:08:52,167
In other words...

122
00:08:53,070 --> 00:08:53,934
bait.

123
00:08:55,473 --> 00:08:58,909
Right. If we delay them,

124
00:08:58,976 --> 00:09:01,342
they won't be able to grasp
the positions of the remaining three.

125
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:04,774
If we do that, we'll be able
to shake off our pursuers,

126
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:06,543
but the one who has become
the bait will probably...

127
00:09:10,655 --> 00:09:11,417
die.

128
00:09:44,255 --> 00:09:45,950
So, who's going to do it?

129
00:09:52,263 --> 00:09:54,629
We need the dog to follow Sasuke.

130
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:56,925
That means...

131
00:10:04,008 --> 00:10:05,305
Fine...

132
00:10:06,043 --> 00:10:08,034
- I'II...
- I guess it has to be me.

133
00:10:08,379 --> 00:10:09,277
Shikamaru?!

134
00:10:09,914 --> 00:10:11,472
W-Why you?!

135
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:14,983
It's better than being wiped out, right?

136
00:10:16,087 --> 00:10:17,054
Besides, among us,

137
00:10:17,421 --> 00:10:19,480
the only one who is equal
to playing the bait

138
00:10:19,557 --> 00:10:22,355
and who has the possibility
of surviving...

139
00:10:24,729 --> 00:10:26,720
is me.

140
00:10:30,501 --> 00:10:34,597
Shadow Possession Jutsu is an Art
originally intended as a delay tactic, so...

141
00:10:35,673 --> 00:10:37,868
Well, I'll catch up later!

142
00:10:38,576 --> 00:10:39,873
Now get going

143
00:10:45,383 --> 00:10:47,578
We're counting on you, Shikamaru!

144
00:10:50,688 --> 00:10:51,484
Sakura!

145
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:56,719
Yeah.

146
00:11:05,469 --> 00:11:08,927
<i>Was Shikamaru ever this reliable</i>
<i>of a character?</i>

147
00:11:13,511 --> 00:11:14,535
<i>Be careful...</i>

148
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:16,776
<i>Shikamaru.</i>

149
00:11:45,176 --> 00:11:47,838
No matter how much you try to erase
the signs of your presence...

150
00:11:50,781 --> 00:11:51,907
you're in plain view.

151
00:11:56,787 --> 00:11:59,585
Hey! The enemy is approaching fast.

152
00:11:59,957 --> 00:12:01,049
What did you say?!

153
00:12:01,659 --> 00:12:04,287
I wonder if he's really
delaying the enemy.

154
00:12:06,297 --> 00:12:08,765
<i>Me with the number one cold feet!</i>

155
00:12:09,834 --> 00:12:11,563
Don't tell me, Shikamaru...

156
00:12:12,136 --> 00:12:14,366
Shikamaru will be okay!

157
00:12:15,172 --> 00:12:17,037
Don't tell me, he ran away.

158
00:12:17,808 --> 00:12:19,901
I said he'll be okay!

159
00:12:20,111 --> 00:12:21,100
What'll be okay?!

160
00:12:21,178 --> 00:12:24,375
He has a dirty mouth and
always says stuff is a pain.

161
00:12:24,749 --> 00:12:26,580
But he wouldn't betray us!

162
00:12:29,186 --> 00:12:32,314
He hardly ever says
he'll do something himself,

163
00:12:32,656 --> 00:12:34,419
but he makes sure to do it
if he says it!

164
00:12:34,792 --> 00:12:36,589
That's absolute.

165
00:12:37,128 --> 00:12:40,120
<i>I want to believe...</i>
<i>I want to believe, but...</i>

166
00:12:41,632 --> 00:12:42,929
Pick up the pace!

167
00:12:51,842 --> 00:12:54,333
I somehow managed to
get away completely.

168
00:13:00,518 --> 00:13:01,917
Their strides are irregular.

169
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:05,316
Urgency is probably increasing
their fatigue.

170
00:13:18,669 --> 00:13:19,727
Sorry about that.

171
00:13:20,504 --> 00:13:23,632
I was supposed to be the guy
with the number one cold feet.

172
00:13:25,643 --> 00:13:29,079
It seems my character has
changed just a bit this time.

173
00:13:31,115 --> 00:13:32,844
The fact that I'm tired is true.

174
00:13:33,284 --> 00:13:34,945
Those footprints are wrong.

175
00:13:36,287 --> 00:13:39,882
By the way, this is what
the dog's paw print really is.

176
00:13:51,235 --> 00:13:53,533
Oh, he's still a kid.

177
00:13:54,071 --> 00:13:56,437
To think we'd all get caught like this.

178
00:13:57,007 --> 00:14:00,465
So this is the rumored Leaf Village's
Shadow Paralysis Jutsu, huh?

179
00:14:02,346 --> 00:14:04,371
That's an old way of saying it!

180
00:14:05,349 --> 00:14:07,146
The times are passing!

181
00:14:07,551 --> 00:14:11,078
It's called Shadow Possession Jutsu now,
old man.

182
00:14:15,059 --> 00:14:17,721
<i>Sure enough,</i>
<i>that match wasn't good.</i>

183
00:14:27,371 --> 00:14:31,671
<i>I used too much Chakra.</i>
<i>I can't hang on much longer...</i>

184
00:14:35,513 --> 00:14:38,880
<i>1, 2, 3, 4...</i>

185
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:43,350
<i>5, 6, 7...8.</i>

186
00:14:43,888 --> 00:14:44,786
<i>Eight people...</i>

187
00:14:45,789 --> 00:14:48,656
<i>Eight... No, there's one more...</i>

188
00:14:49,326 --> 00:14:50,850
<i>There are nine people following us.</i>

189
00:14:52,396 --> 00:14:56,799
<i>Sure enough, the ninth person's role is</i>
<i>to protect against them getting ambushed.</i>

190
00:14:57,701 --> 00:14:59,498
<i>That person stays at a fixed distance,</i>

191
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:02,733
<i>moves in the back and responds</i>
<i>to an enemy attack.</i>

192
00:15:10,147 --> 00:15:15,881
<i>But...this will make clear where</i>
<i>that person's hiding!</i>

193
00:15:31,635 --> 00:15:32,499
<i>There, huh?!</i>

194
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:40,010
<i>Dang it... The Shadow won't reach.</i>

195
00:15:40,711 --> 00:15:43,145
<i>I don't have the stamina to</i>
<i>send it to Chakra.</i>

196
00:15:44,481 --> 00:15:47,678
It's futile. I see through your technique.

197
00:15:50,921 --> 00:15:52,115
<i>Is this as far as it goes?</i>

198
00:15:52,890 --> 00:15:55,154
It looks like you're at your limit...

199
00:15:55,659 --> 00:15:58,184
This Shadow Possession Jutsu
is going to break very soon.

200
00:15:58,729 --> 00:15:59,821
Prepare yourself!

201
00:16:11,508 --> 00:16:14,773
<i>I wanted to...</i>
<i>become a Ninja any which way,</i>

202
00:16:15,179 --> 00:16:16,771
<i>save up money any which way,</i>

203
00:16:17,114 --> 00:16:19,446
<i>get married any which way to</i>
<i>an ordinary woman</i>

204
00:16:19,516 --> 00:16:21,177
<i>who's neither beautiful nor ugly</i>

205
00:16:21,585 --> 00:16:23,416
<i>and have two kids any which way.</i>

206
00:16:23,921 --> 00:16:26,947
<i>First will be a girl, and then a boy...</i>

207
00:16:27,791 --> 00:16:30,760
<i>I would retire from being a Ninja</i>
<i>when my eldest daughter marries</i>

208
00:16:30,828 --> 00:16:32,420
<i>and my son becomes a full fledged man.</i>

209
00:16:32,896 --> 00:16:36,388
<i>And then I take it easy</i>
<i>in my life of retirement</i>

210
00:16:36,467 --> 00:16:38,901
<i>playing Japanese chess</i>
<i>and Go the whole day.</i>

211
00:16:39,637 --> 00:16:42,071
<i>Then I die of old age before my wife.</i>

212
00:16:43,407 --> 00:16:45,375
<i>Such a life would've been nice.</i>

213
00:16:45,709 --> 00:16:48,234
<i>I was out of character,</i>
<i>I tried too hard this time.</i>

214
00:16:48,946 --> 00:16:50,811
<i>I wanted it to end in an ordinary way.</i>

215
00:16:52,816 --> 00:16:54,841
<i>What I did was a drag...</i>

216
00:16:58,088 --> 00:17:01,182
Hmm, the movements of
our pursuers have stopped.

217
00:17:01,825 --> 00:17:05,454
Yes! The delaying was a success!

218
00:17:06,330 --> 00:17:07,262
Shikamaru, eh?

219
00:17:08,632 --> 00:17:11,362
<i>I'm sorry I doubted you, even a little.</i>

220
00:17:12,369 --> 00:17:13,097
<i>Okay!</i>

221
00:17:14,271 --> 00:17:17,297
<i>Now...you wait, Sasuke.</i>

222
00:17:19,009 --> 00:17:21,170
<i>And...Shikamaru...</i>

223
00:17:22,046 --> 00:17:24,480
<i>Live, and catch up to us no matter what!</i>

224
00:17:27,885 --> 00:17:30,945
As you say, it seems I'm at my limit.

225
00:17:41,632 --> 00:17:43,930
Hey, come on out.

226
00:17:48,839 --> 00:17:51,501
While you're at it, cut off his head.

227
00:18:07,691 --> 00:18:09,591
I finally caught up.

228
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:12,057
A-Asuma?! Why?

229
00:19:08,952 --> 00:19:11,716
Well done, Shikamaru.

230
00:19:16,427 --> 00:19:18,418
Sure enough, out of character.

231
00:19:20,097 --> 00:19:22,998
<i>For the time being, you retire here.</i>

232
00:19:28,972 --> 00:19:29,700
Hurry!

233
00:19:36,513 --> 00:19:38,208
<i>What a pest.</i>

234
00:19:41,018 --> 00:19:44,852
<i>The pursuers have increased?</i>
<i>Two? No, three?</i>

235
00:19:45,722 --> 00:19:47,485
Kankuro! Pick up the pace!

236
00:19:48,525 --> 00:19:49,287
Okay.

237
00:19:57,434 --> 00:19:58,628
<i>I won't let you get away.</i>

238
00:20:02,639 --> 00:20:05,437
<i>Don't jump the gun, Sasuke.</i>

239
00:20:07,277 --> 00:20:08,039
<i>Sasuke.</i>

240
00:20:56,860 --> 00:20:59,158
Now then, shall we begin?

241
00:21:05,770 --> 00:21:15,839
<i>Everyone makes mistakes</i>
<i>It's nothing to be ashamed about</i>

242
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:27,123
<i>Don't let this scar be for naught</i>
<i>Walk with a smile</i>

243
00:21:37,234 --> 00:21:42,866
<i>Yes, breathe in the air</i>
<i>Lift your face to the sky and jump</i>

244
00:21:42,940 --> 00:21:47,900
<i>If it rains, take a break</i>
<i>Go where the wind takes you</i>

245
00:21:48,279 --> 00:21:53,182
<i>So many regrets</i>
<i>Don't let this scar be for naught</i>

246
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:58,381
<i>Let's go carve the badges in our chest</i>
<i>Yes, it's Show Time, life begins now.</i>

247
00:21:58,456 --> 00:22:08,627
<i>Everyone makes mistakes</i>
<i>It's nothing to be ashamed about</i>

248
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:19,366
<i>Don't let this scar be for naught</i>
<i>Walk with a smile</i>

249
00:22:19,443 --> 00:22:30,012
